stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR
    [*] --> Soft

    Soft: SOFT MARKET
    note right of Soft
        - Plentiful capacity
        - Rates declining
        - Broad coverage
        - Loose terms
        - Combined ratio rising
        - Underwriting discipline erodes
    end note

    Soft --> LossEvent: Catastrophe,<br/>adverse development,<br/>or capital exit

    LossEvent: TRIGGERING EVENT
    note right of LossEvent
        - Hurricane / earthquake
        - Social inflation surge
        - Reinsurance market turn
        - Investment losses
    end note

    LossEvent --> Hard: Surplus depleted,<br/>capacity contracts

    Hard: HARD MARKET
    note right of Hard
        - Scarce capacity
        - Rates rising sharply
        - Tighter terms
        - Higher deductibles
        - Exclusions expanded
        - Combined ratio improves
    end note

    Hard --> NewCapital: Profitability attracts<br/>new capital

    NewCapital: RECOVERY
    note right of NewCapital
        - Primary insurers rebuild surplus
        - New entrants form
        - ILS and alt capital flows in
        - Reinsurance capacity expands
    end note

    NewCapital --> Soft: Competition restored,<br/>rates begin declining

    Hard --> Hard: Losses continue<br/>(extended hard cycle)
    Soft --> Soft: Steady state<br/>(extended soft cycle)
